Class VaccineBST

  • java.lang.Object
    • VaccineBST
  • public class VaccineBST
extends java.lang.Object
    Class used to extract data from vaccinations.csv and add it to a Binary Search Tree (BST) containing Vaccine objects accordingly. This class also uses the BST find method to determine whether an inputted country and date combination appears in the BST. 02/03/2022

      void extractData()
      Reads the data from the vaccinations.csv file and appends the consequently created Vaccine objects to the BST created above.
      Vaccine findVax​(Vaccine v)
      Method used to determine whether a provided Vaccine object, created with a country and date combination provided by the user, is present in the BST of Vaccine objects.
      int getFOpCount()
      Method used to return the find operation counter retrieved from the BST program that counts the number of comparisons done by the BST operations when performing the find operations.
      int getIOpCount()
      Method used to return the insert operation counter retrieved from the BST program that counts the number of comparisons done by the BST operations when inserting all the Vaccination items.

      • extractData

        public void extractData()
        Reads the data from the vaccinations.csv file and appends the consequently created Vaccine objects to the BST created above.

      • findVax

        public Vaccine findVax​(Vaccine v)
        Method used to determine whether a provided Vaccine object, created with a country and date combination provided by the user, is present in the BST of Vaccine objects.
        Parameters:
        v - Vaccine object provided that is compared against Vaccine objects in the BST.
        Returns:
        Vaccine object if one that matches the argument provided is found; null if it is not found.

      • getIOpCount

        public int getIOpCount()
        Method used to return the insert operation counter retrieved from the BST program that counts the number of comparisons done by the BST operations when inserting all the Vaccination items. This method make it readily available to VaccineBSTApp.
        Returns:
        Integer value of the insert operation counter from the BST program.

      • getFOpCount

        public int getFOpCount()
        Method used to return the find operation counter retrieved from the BST program that counts the number of comparisons done by the BST operations when performing the find operations. This method make it readily available to VaccineBSTApp.
        Returns:
        Integer value of the find operation counter from the BST program.
